
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-nitinb-mpls-tp-lsp-ping-bfd-procedures-02.txt'>
    <title>"LSP-Ping and BFD encapsulation over ACH", Nitin Bahadur, Rahul Aggarwal, David Ward, Thomas Nadeau, Nurit Sprecher, Yaacov Weingarten</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-nitinb-mpls-tp-lsp-ping-bfd-procedures-02.txt</link>
    <description>LSP-Ping and BFD for MPLS are existing and widely deployment OAM mechanisms for MPLS LSPs.  This document describes ACH encapsulation for LSP-Ping, to enable use of LSP-Ping when IP addressing is not in use.  This document also clarifies the use of BFD for MPLS LSPs using ACH encapsulation, when IP addressing may not be available and/or it may not be desirable to encapsulate BFD packets in IP.</description>
    <dc:date>2010-02-15T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
